<TITLE> Court frames looting charges against Amini <b> RECAST </b> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 11 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court has framed charges of looting of property against nine including Islami Oikya Jote chairman Mufti Mohammed Fazlul Haque Amini in a case regarding disputes over the Waqf property of a Lalbagh madrasa. Magistrate Faisal Atik Bin Kader of Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court, Dhaka framed the charges on Sunday. Seven defendants including Amini pleaded not guilty after the charges were read out. Two of the accused, Mizanur Rahman and Saiful Islam, are at large. The case was filed on Feb 27, 2007 by Abdur Rashid Ahammad, Motwali of the Waqf property and principal of Husainia Ashraful Ulum madrasa at Barakatra in Lalbagh. According to the statement of the case, on June 9, 2003 the defendants including Amini carrying arms stormed the house of Ahammad at 101 Abu Hasnat Road, Saat Rawja. They looted assets worth Tk 30 lakh including gold ornaments and cash at gunpoint. They assaulted and molested the wife and two sisters-in-law of the plaintiff. The other defendants are Abu Tayeb, Abul Khayer, Md Ali Hossain, Shafikur Rahman, Khaled Mosharraf and Hedayet Ullah. The deposition has been set for March 7 next year. Amini's lawyers Joynal Abedin Mesbah and Mahiuddin Chowdhury said there are two other criminal cases against Amini. b
